R notebook of a manuscript entitled "Long-term effects of regular physical activity and exercise habits in patients with early-stage Parkinson's disease."

(1) CSV files used in this study

We used follwing csvs that were deposited in PPMI database to create the combined file (“UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS.csv”) which was used for subsequent analyses.

“Primary_Diagnosis”:This file contains the information regarding diagnosis of enrolled participants. This file was used to identify PD and HC patients. The “PRIMDIAG” column was used to identify PD and control participants (“01”=PD patients, “17”=control participants).

“PASE_-_Leisure_Time_Activity.csv”, “PASE_-_Household_Activity.csv”: This CSV contains the information regarding the result of PASE questionnaire. We calculated the PASE leisure, PASE household, and PASE work scores, as described in Washburn RA et al., 1993, 1999. We also quantified moderate-to-vigorous exercise levels using the sum of the scores from question 4, which quantified moderate sports and recreational activities in the past week, and question 5, which quantified intense sports and recreational activities in the past week, as well as the percentage of participants who met the recommendations of AAN quality metrics.

“Screening___Demographics.csv”: This is the CSV that incooporates the information regarding the background characteristics of enrolled participants.

“PD_Features.csv”: This file contains the baseline information of PD patients such as date of diagnosis.

“Concomitant_Medications.csv”: This file is the log of the PD-related medications. This file was used to calculate LEDD.

“MDS_UPDRS_Part_I.csv”, “MDS_UPDRS_Part_I__Patient_Questionnaire.csv”, “MDS_UPDRS_Part_II__Patient_Questionnaire.csv”“, ”MDS_UPDRS_Part_III.csv“, ”MDS_UPDRS_Part_IV.csv"*: These files contain information regarding MDS-UPDRS scores.

“Montreal_Cognitive_Assessment_MoCA.csv”, “SCOPA-AUT.csv”,“Epworth_Sleepiness_Scale.csv”, “Modified_Schwab_+_England_ADL.csv”, “REM_Sleep_Disorder_Questionnaire.csv”, “Hopkins_Verbal_Learning_Test.csv”, “Benton_Judgment_of_Line_Orientation.csv”, “Letter_-_Number_Sequencing__PD_.csv”, “Symbol_Digit_Modalities.csv”, “Geriatric_Depression_Scale_Short.csv”: These files contains information regarding Montreal Cognitive Assessment, Scales for Outcomes in Parkinson’s Disease-Autonomic Dysfunction, Epworth Sleepiness Scale, Modified Schwab & England Activity of Daily Living scale, REM sleep Behavior Disorder Screening Questionnaire, Hopkins Verbal Learning Test-Revised, Judgment of Line Orientation, Letter-Number Sequencing, Symbol Digit Modalities Test, and Geriatric Depression Scale, respectively.

(2) The column name of csv called “UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS.csv”

The column names of "" was as follows

“PATNO”:This is the identification number.

“EVENT_ID”: This is the EVENT_ID information when the data was obtained.

“Age”: This is the patient age when the data was obtained.

“Sex” : This is the patient sex information.

“Disease_duration_symptom”:This is information regarding the disease duration from the symptom onset when the data was obtained.

“Disease_duration_diagnosis”：This is information regarding the disease duration from the diganosis when the data was obtained.

“PASE_Leisure_score”: This is information regarding the PASE Leisure subscore when the data was obtained.

“PASE_Household_score”: This is information regarding the PASE household subscore when the data was obtained.

“PASE_Work_score”: This is information regarding the PASE work subscore when the data was obtained.

“PASE_Total_score”: This is information regarding the PASE total score when the data was obtained.

“Group”: This is information whether this patient was PD patients (“PD”) or HCs (“Control”).

“Elapsed_months”: This is information regarding months from the baseline of the original PPMI study when the data was obtained.

“Elapsed_months_2”: This is information regarding months from the baseline of this study when the data was obtained.

“AE”: This is the summation of raw scores of score4 and score5 in the PASE questionnaire when the data was obtained.

“AAN_criteria”: This is the information wheter this patient met AAN criteria (“Meet” or “Not”) when the data was obtained.

“LEDD_sum”: This is information regarding LEDD when the data was obtained.

“sum_Tremor_score”: This is information regarding MDS-UPDRS tremor subscore when the data was obtained.

“sum_PIGD_score”: This is information regarding MDS-UPDRS `tremor PIGD subscore when the data was obtained.

“sum_UPDRS_total_score”: This is information regarding MDS-UPDRS total score when the data was obtained.

"MOCA_Total_score: This is information regarding MoCA total score when the data was obtained.

“ESS_total_score”: This is information regarding ESS total score when the data was obtained.

“MSEADLG”: This is information regarding MSE-ADL total score when the data was obtained.

“RBDSQ_total_score”: This is information regarding RBDSQ total score when the data was obtained.

“SCOPA_total_score”: This is information regarding SCOPA-AUT total score when the data was obtained.

“HVLT_DELAYED_RECALL_T”:This is information regarding HVLT-R delayed recall T score when the data was obtained.

“JLO_RAW”: This is information regarding JLO total score when the data was obtained.

“LNS_RAW”: This is information regarding LNS total score when the data was obtained.

“SDMT_correct”: This is information regarding SDMT total score when the data was obtained.

“GDS_total_score”: This is information regarding GDS-15 total score when the data was obtained.


We first downloaded the libraries which we used.

library(tidyverse); library(plyr); library(gtsummary);library(lubridate);library(lme4);library(MatchIt);library(tableone);library(spearmanCI);library(stringr);library(Amelia)



We then read “UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS.csv”.

UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS<-readr::read_csv("./UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS.csv") %>% suppressMessages()



We calculated the follow-up years.

UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS %>% filter(Elapsed_months_2==0) %>% filter(is.na(sum_UPDRS_part3)==F)->a
UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS %>% filter(is.element(PATNO,a$PATNO))->UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS

c<-c()
for(i in unique(UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS$PATNO)){
  UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS %>% filter(PATNO==i) -> a;
  if ((nrow(a)>=3))(append(c,a$PATNO[1])->c)
}
UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS <- UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS %>% dplyr::filter(is.element(PATNO,c))

UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS_PD<-UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS %>% filter(Group=="PD")

Average_follow.ups<-c()
for(i in unique(UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS_PD$PATNO)){
  UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS_PD %>% dplyr::filter(PATNO==i) ->a;
  Average_follow.ups<-append(Average_follow.ups,a$Elapsed_months_2[nrow(a)])
}

paste("the median follow-up duration from the baseline of our study were ", quantile(Average_follow.ups/12,0.5), " years [interquartile range (IQR):", quantile(Average_follow.ups/12,0.25),"–",quantile(Average_follow.ups/12,0.75), " years]",sep="")
[1] "the median follow-up duration from the baseline of our study were 5 years [interquartile range (IQR):4–6 years]"

We created Fig.1A using following codes.

UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS %>% dplyr::filter(Elapsed_months_2<=72) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=Elapsed_months_2/12,y=PASE_Total_score,colour=Group)) + theme_classic() + stat_smooth(se=T,fullrange = T,level =
                                                                                                       0.95,method=lm,alpha=0.1,size=2)+
  xlab("Elapsed years")+ylab("PASE total score")+scale_colour_discrete(name="")+scale_color_manual(values = c("#00BFC4","#F8766D"))
Scale for 'colour' is already present. Adding another scale for 'colour', which will replace the existing scale.
`geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'



We created Fig.1B using following codes.


UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS %>% dplyr::filter(Group=="Control") %>% dplyr::filter(Elapsed_months_2<=72) %>% group_by(Elapsed_months_2) %>% dplyr::mutate(perc=100*sum(AAN_criteria=="Meet")/sum(is.na(AAN_criteria)==F)) ->f
UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS %>% dplyr::filter(Group=="PD") %>% dplyr::filter(Elapsed_months_2<=72) %>% group_by(Elapsed_months_2) %>% dplyr::mutate(perc=100*sum(AAN_criteria=="Meet")/sum(is.na(AAN_criteria)==F))->g
data.frame(label=c(rep("Control",7),rep("PD",7)),prec=c(unique(f$perc),unique(g$perc)),yr=c(seq(0,6),seq(0,6))) %>% ggplot(aes(x=yr,y=prec,colour=label))+geom_line()+theme_classic()+ylim(0,100)+xlab("Elapsed years")+ylab("Percentage of patients who met AAN quality metrics for regular excercise regimen")+scale_color_manual(values = c("#00BFC4","#F8766D"))



The first half of results for the section “Clinical characteristics of PD patients” can be obtained with the following code.

summary_trend<-UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS %>% dplyr::filter((Elapsed_months_2<=72)&(Group=="PD")) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(Elapsed_months_3=Elapsed_months_2/12) %>% with(lm(PASE_Total_score~Elapsed_months_3)) %>% summary()

summry_spearman<-UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS %>% dplyr::filter((Elapsed_months_2<=72)&(Group=="PD")) %>%
  with(cor.test(PASE_Total_score,Elapsed_months_2,method="spearman")) %>% suppressWarnings()

summry_spearmanCI<-UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS %>% dplyr::filter((Elapsed_months_2<=72)&(Group=="PD")) %>%
  with(spearmanCI(PASE_Total_score,Elapsed_months_2)) %>% capture.output()
summry_spearmanCI<-summry_spearmanCI[3] %>% str_split(pattern=" ")
summry_spearmanCI[[1]]->summry_spearmanCI
append(summry_spearmanCI[2],summry_spearmanCI[3]) %>% as.numeric()->summry_spearmanCI

paste("During the follow-up period, overall regular physical activity level of PD patients gradually decreased with the PASE total score decreasing by ",as.character(round(summary_trend$coefficients[2,][1],2))," points per year [95% CI,",as.character(round(summary_trend$coefficients[2,][1]-1.96*summary_trend$coefficients[2,][2],2))," to ",as.character(round(summary_trend$coefficients[2,][1]+1.96*summary_trend$coefficients[2,][2],2)),"; Spearman’s rho = ",round(summry_spearman$estimate,2), "(95% CI, ", round(summry_spearmanCI[1],2)," to ",round(summry_spearmanCI[1],2), "), P = ", round(summry_spearman$p.value,3),")]",sep="")
[1] "During the follow-up period, overall regular physical activity level of PD patients gradually decreased with the PASE total score decreasing by -4.46 points per year [95% CI,-7.28 to -1.63; Spearman’s rho = -0.08(95% CI, -0.14 to -0.14), P = 0.002)]"

summary_trend<-UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS %>% dplyr::filter((Elapsed_months_2<=72)&(Group=="Control")) %>%

paste("no significant change was observed longitudinally in HCs [Spearman’s rho = ",round(summry_spearman$estimate,2), " (95% CI, ", round(summry_spearmanCI[1],2)," to ",round(summry_spearmanCI[1],2), "), P = ", round(summry_spearman$p.value,3),"]",sep="")

  with(cor.test(AE,Elapsed_months_2,method="spearman"))%>% suppressWarnings()

  with(spearmanCI(AE,Elapsed_months_2)) %>% capture.output()

summry_spearmanCI[[1]]->summry_spearmanCI

summary_trend_NCs<-UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS %>% dplyr::filter((Elapsed_months_2<=72)&(Group=="Control")) %>% with(cor.test(AE,Elapsed_months_2,method="spearman"))%>% suppressWarnings()

summry_spearmanCI_NCs<-UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS %>% dplyr::filter((Elapsed_months_2<=72)&(Group=="Control")) %>%
  with(spearmanCI(AE,Elapsed_months_2)) %>% capture.output()

max_follow.up<-c();PATNO<-c();Final.visit<-c()
for (i in unique(a$PATNO)){
  a %>% dplyr::filter(PATNO==i) ->a1;
  max_follow.up<-append(max_follow.up,max(a1$`Elapsed years`));
  PATNO<-append(PATNO,i);difftime(min(a1$`Final visit`),Sys.Date()) %>% as.numeric->b1
  Final.visit<-append(Final.visit,b1)
}

a<-data.frame(PATNO=PATNO,follow.max=max_follow.up,Baseline=Final.visit) %>% as_tibble() %>% dplyr::mutate(follow=if_else(follow.max>=6,"follow up for 6 years","follow up for 5 years or less")) %>% dplyr::select(PATNO,follow,Baseline) %>% dplyr::right_join(a,by="PATNO") %>%dplyr::filter(`Elapsed years`==0)

At the table above, the difference in baseline dates were expressed as the time from today to the baseline dates, therefore, we change these values to “baseline date”.

a %>% dplyr::filter(follow=="follow up for 5 years or less")->short
short$Baseline %>% quantile() -> short
Sys.Date()+short->short

a %>% dplyr::filter(follow=="follow up for 6 years")->long
long$Baseline %>% quantile() -> long
Sys.Date()+long->long

paste("Baseline dates, ",short[3]," (",short[2],"–",short[4],") (follow up for 6 years) vs. ",long[3]," (",long[2],"–",long[4],") (follow up for 5 years or less)")
[1] "Baseline dates,  2014-06-30  ( 2014-02-28 – 2014-12-16 ) (follow up for 6 years) vs.  2013-07-31  ( 2013-05-31 – 2013-11-30 ) (follow up for 5 years or less)"


Main result (1): the interaction effect between regular physical activity levels at the baseline and clinical progression.

After the following code, “interaction_effect_table_baseline_final.csv” will be obtained, and this csv includes the fist half of the main result. Fig.2A is also created using the following code. Fig.2A is also created using the following code. 

###Interaction with baseline_PASE_Total_score, adjusted for Age, LEDD, Disease duration, Sex
UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS_PD<-UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS %>% filter(Group=="PD")
c<-c()
for(i in unique(UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS_PD$PATNO)){
  UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS_PD %>% filter(PATNO==i) -> a;
  append(c,rep(a$PASE_Total_score[1],nrow(a)))->c
}
c->baseline_PASE_Total_score
UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS_PD<-cbind(UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS_PD,baseline_PASE_Total_score) %>% as_tibble()

a<-UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS_PD %>% dplyr::select(PATNO,Sex,Elapsed_months_2,baseline_PASE_Total_score,Age,LEDD_sum,sum_UPDRS_part3,sum_Tremor_score,sum_PIGD_score,MOCA_Total_score,HVLT_DELAYED_RECALL_T,JLO_RAW,LNS_RAW,SDMT_correct,SCOPA_total_score,GDS_total_score, ESS_total_score,RBDSQ_total_score,MSEADLG,Disease_duration_symptom)
Partner<-c()
c<-c()
for(i in colnames(a)){
  if((i!="Elapsed_months_2")&(i!="baseline_PASE_Total_score")&(i!="Age")&(i!="PATNO")&(i!="LEDD_sum")&(i!="Disease_duration_symptom")&(i!="Sex")){
    a %>% dplyr::select(i,Elapsed_months_2,baseline_PASE_Total_score,Age,PATNO,LEDD_sum,Disease_duration_symptom,Sex)->a1;
    colnames(a1)<-c("V1","Elapsed_months_2","baseline_PASE_Total_score","Age","PATNO","LEDD_sum","Disease_duration_symptom","Sex");
    a1$V1<-scale(a1$V1,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$baseline_PASE_Total_score<-scale(a1$baseline_PASE_Total_score,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Age<-scale(a1$Age,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Elapsed_months_2<-scale(a1$Elapsed_months_2,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$LEDD_sum<-scale(a1$LEDD_sum,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Disease_duration_symptom<-scale(a1$Disease_duration_symptom,center=T,scale=T);
    with(a1,lmer(V1~Elapsed_months_2*baseline_PASE_Total_score+Age+LEDD_sum+Disease_duration_symptom+Sex+(1+Elapsed_months_2|PATNO),REML=FALSE))->b;
    summary(b)->b.summary;confint(b,method="b",nsim=1000) %>% suppressMessages()->b.confint;
    b.summary$coefficients[8,]->e;b.confint[10,]->f;b.summary$AICtab[1:2]->A.BIC
    with(a1,lmer(V1~Elapsed_months_2+baseline_PASE_Total_score+Age+LEDD_sum+Disease_duration_symptom+Sex+(1+Elapsed_months_2|PATNO),REML=FALSE))->b.null;
    anova(b,b.null)->d;summary(b.null)->d.summary;d.summary$AICtab[1:2]-b.summary$AICtab[1:2]->A.BIC
    c(e[1],e[2],e[3],f[1],f[2],d$`Pr(>Chisq)`[2]*65,A.BIC)->d;
    bind_rows(c,d) %>% suppressMessages()->c;
    append(Partner,i)->Partner
  }}
colnames(c)[6]<-"p.value"
cbind(Partner,c)->interaction_effect_table_baseline_PASE_Total_score
interaction_effect_table_baseline_PASE_Total_score <-interaction_effect_table_baseline_PASE_Total_score %>% mutate(significance=if_else(`p.value`<=0.05,"Significant","Not"))
interaction_effect_table_baseline_PASE_Total_score <-cbind(interaction_effect_table_baseline_PASE_Total_score,class=rep("baseline_PASE_Total_score",nrow(interaction_effect_table_baseline_PASE_Total_score )))

###Interaction with baseline_PASE_Work_score, adjusted for Age, LEDD, Disease duration, Sex
c<-c()

a<-UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS_PD %>% dplyr::select(PATNO,Sex,Elapsed_months_2,baseline_PASE_Work_score,Age,LEDD_sum,sum_UPDRS_part3,sum_Tremor_score,sum_PIGD_score,MOCA_Total_score,HVLT_DELAYED_RECALL_T,JLO_RAW,LNS_RAW,SDMT_correct,SCOPA_total_score,GDS_total_score, ESS_total_score,RBDSQ_total_score,MSEADLG,Disease_duration_symptom)
Partner<-c()
c<-c()
for(i in colnames(a)){
  if((i!="Elapsed_months_2")&(i!="baseline_PASE_Work_score")&(i!="Age")&(i!="PATNO")&(i!="LEDD_sum")&(i!="Disease_duration_symptom")&(i!="Sex")){
    a %>% dplyr::select(i,Elapsed_months_2,baseline_PASE_Work_score,Age,PATNO,LEDD_sum,Disease_duration_symptom,Sex)->a1;
    colnames(a1)<-c("V1","Elapsed_months_2","baseline_PASE_Work_score","Age","PATNO","LEDD_sum","Disease_duration_symptom","Sex");
    a1$V1<-scale(a1$V1,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$baseline_PASE_Work_score<-scale(a1$baseline_PASE_Work_score,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Age<-scale(a1$Age,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Elapsed_months_2<-scale(a1$Elapsed_months_2,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$LEDD_sum<-scale(a1$LEDD_sum,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Disease_duration_symptom<-scale(a1$Disease_duration_symptom,center=T,scale=T);
    with(a1,lmer(V1~Elapsed_months_2*baseline_PASE_Work_score+Age+LEDD_sum+Disease_duration_symptom+Sex+(1+Elapsed_months_2|PATNO),REML=FALSE))->b;
    summary(b)->b.summary;confint(b,method="b",nsim=1000) %>% suppressMessages()->b.confint;
    b.summary$coefficients[8,]->e;b.confint[10,]->f;b.summary$AICtab[1:2]->A.BIC
    with(a1,lmer(V1~Elapsed_months_2+baseline_PASE_Work_score+Age+LEDD_sum+Disease_duration_symptom+Sex+(1+Elapsed_months_2|PATNO),REML=FALSE))->b.null;
    anova(b,b.null)->d;summary(b.null)->d.summary;d.summary$AICtab[1:2]-b.summary$AICtab[1:2]->A.BIC
    c(e[1],e[2],e[3],f[1],f[2],d$`Pr(>Chisq)`[2]*65,A.BIC)->d;
    bind_rows(c,d) %>% suppressMessages()->c;
    append(Partner,i)->Partner
  }}
colnames(c)[6]<-"p.value"
cbind(Partner,c)->interaction_effect_table_baseline_PASE_Work_score

interaction_effect_table_baseline_final$Partner_2<-rep(c("MDS-UPDRS part3 score","MDS-UPDRS tremor subscore","MDS-UPDRS PIGD subscore","MOCA total score","HVLT delayed recall T score","JLO total score","LNS total score","SDMT total score","SCOPA-AUT total score","GDS total score", "ESS total score","RBDSQ total score","MSE percent ADLscore"),5)
interaction_effect_table_baseline_final$Partner_2<-factor(interaction_effect_table_baseline_final$Partner_2,levels=rev(c("MDS-UPDRS part3 score","MDS-UPDRS tremor subscore","MDS-UPDRS PIGD subscore","MOCA total score","HVLT delayed recall T score","JLO total score","LNS total score","SDMT total score","SCOPA-AUT total score","GDS total score", "ESS total score","RBDSQ total score","MSE percent ADLscore")))
interaction_effect_table_baseline_final$class<-factor(interaction_effect_table_baseline_final$class,levels=c("baseline_PASE_Total_score","baseline_PASE_Leisure_score","baseline_PASE_Household_score","baseline_PASE_Work_score","baseline_AE"))
interaction_effect_table_baseline_final %>% ggplot(aes(y=`Partner_2`,x=class,fill=abs(`t value`))) + theme_classic()+ geom_tile()+scale_fill_gradient(low="white",high="red",name="t value",limits = c(0, 5.5))+geom_point(aes(shape=significance))+scale_shape_manual(values = c(32,8),labels=c("","significant",""),name="")+ylab("")+xlab("")


write_csv(interaction_effect_table_baseline_final,"interaction_effect_table_baseline_final.csv")


Main result (2): the interaction effect between average regular physical activity levels over follow-up periods and clinical progression.

After the following code, “interaction_effect_table_mean_final.csv” will be obtained, and this csv includes the fist half of the main result. Fig.2A is also created using the following code.

a<-UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS_PD %>% dplyr::select(PATNO,Sex,Elapsed_months_2,mean_PASE_Work_score,Age,LEDD_sum,sum_UPDRS_part3,sum_Tremor_score,sum_PIGD_score,MOCA_Total_score,HVLT_DELAYED_RECALL_T,JLO_RAW,LNS_RAW,SDMT_correct,SCOPA_total_score,GDS_total_score, ESS_total_score,RBDSQ_total_score,MSEADLG,Disease_duration_symptom)
a$Sex<-as.factor(a$Sex)
Partner<-c()
c<-c()
for(i in colnames(a)){
  if((i!="Elapsed_months_2")&(i!="mean_PASE_Work_score")&(i!="Age")&(i!="PATNO")&(i!="LEDD_sum")&(i!="Disease_duration_symptom")&(i!="Sex")){
    a %>% dplyr::select(i,Elapsed_months_2,mean_PASE_Work_score,Age,PATNO,LEDD_sum,Disease_duration_symptom,Sex)->a1;
    colnames(a1)<-c("V1","Elapsed_months_2","mean_PASE_Work_score","Age","PATNO","LEDD_sum","Disease_duration_symptom","Sex");
    a1$V1<-scale(a1$V1,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$mean_PASE_Work_score<-scale(a1$mean_PASE_Work_score,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Age<-scale(a1$Age,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Elapsed_months_2<-scale(a1$Elapsed_months_2,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$LEDD_sum<-scale(a1$LEDD_sum,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Disease_duration_symptom<-scale(a1$Disease_duration_symptom,center=T,scale=T);
    with(a1,lmer(V1~Elapsed_months_2*mean_PASE_Work_score+Age+LEDD_sum+Disease_duration_symptom+Sex+(1+Elapsed_months_2|PATNO),REML=FALSE))->b;
    summary(b)->b.summary;confint(b,method="b",nsim=1000) %>% suppressMessages()->b.confint;
    b.summary$coefficients[8,]->e;b.confint[10,]->f;b.summary$AICtab[1:2]->A.BIC
    with(a1,lmer(V1~Elapsed_months_2+mean_PASE_Work_score+Age+LEDD_sum+Disease_duration_symptom+Sex+(1+Elapsed_months_2|PATNO),REML=FALSE))->b.null;
    anova(b,b.null)->d;summary(b.null)->d.summary;d.summary$AICtab[1:2]-b.summary$AICtab[1:2]->A.BIC
    c(e[1],e[2],e[3],f[1],f[2],d$`Pr(>Chisq)`[2]*65,A.BIC)->d;
    bind_rows(c,d) %>% suppressMessages()->c;
    append(Partner,i)->Partner
  }}
colnames(c)[6]<-"p.value"
cbind(Partner,c)->interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Work_score
interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Work_score <-interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Work_score %>% mutate(significance=if_else(`p.value`<=0.05,"Significant","Not"))
interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Work_score <-cbind(interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Work_score,class=rep("mean_PASE_Work_score",nrow(interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Work_score)))

  else(append(c,rep(NA,nrow(a)))->c)
}

Sensitivity analysis (1): Propensity score matching

The following codes descibes how the propensity score mathing was performed in this study. After this code, the following csvs are obtained: "“interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Total_score_categorize.csv”“, ”“interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Household_score_categorize.csv”“, ”“interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Work_score_categorize_2.csv”“, ”“interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Work_score_categorize.csv”“, ”“interaction_effect_table_mean_AE_categorize.csv”".

d<-UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS_PD %>% filter(is.na(mean_PASE_Total_score)==F) %>% filter(Elapsed_months_2==0)
c<-c()
for(i in unique(UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS_PD$PATNO)){
  UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS_PD %>% filter(PATNO==i) -> a;
  if ((nrow(a)>=3)){
    if(mean(a$PASE_Total_score,na.rm = T)>=quantile(d$mean_PASE_Total_score,na.rm=T,0.75))(append(c,rep("50-100",nrow(a)))->c)else{
      if(mean(a$PASE_Total_score,na.rm = T)>=quantile(d$mean_PASE_Total_score,na.rm=T,0.5))(append(c,rep("50-100",nrow(a)))->c)else{
        if(mean(a$PASE_Total_score,na.rm = T)>=quantile(d$mean_PASE_Total_score,na.rm=T,0.25))(append(c,rep("0-50",nrow(a)))->c)else(append(c,rep("0-50",nrow(a)))->c)}}}
  else(append(c,rep(NA,nrow(a)))->c)
}
c->mean_PASE_Total_score_binary

a<-d4 %>% dplyr::select(Elapsed_months_2,Age,sum_PIGD_score,MSEADLG,mean_PASE_Total_score_binary,SDMT_correct,PATNO,Sex,LEDD_sum,Disease_duration_symptom)
c<-c()
p.value<-c()
Partner<-c()
Quantile<-c()
confint_sum<-c()
a$mean_PASE_Total_score_binary<-as.factor(a$mean_PASE_Total_score_binary)
for(i in colnames(a)){
  if((i!="Elapsed_months_2")&(i!="mean_PASE_Total_score_binary")&(i!="Age")&(i!="PATNO")&(i!="Sex")&(i!="LEDD_sum")&(i!="Disease_duration_symptom")){
    a %>% dplyr::select(i,Elapsed_months_2,mean_PASE_Total_score_binary,Age,PATNO,Sex,LEDD_sum,Disease_duration_symptom)->a1;
    colnames(a1)<-c("V1","Elapsed_months_2","mean_PASE_Total_score_categorize","Age","PATNO","Sex","LEDD_sum","Disease_duration_symptom");
    a1$V1<-scale(a1$V1,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Age<-scale(a1$Age,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Elapsed_months_2<-scale(a1$Elapsed_months_2,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$LEDD_sum<-scale(a1$LEDD_sum,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Disease_duration_symptom<-scale(a1$Disease_duration_symptom,center=T,scale=T);
    with(a1,lmer(V1~Elapsed_months_2*mean_PASE_Total_score_categorize+Age+LEDD_sum+Disease_duration_symptom+Sex+(1+Elapsed_months_2|PATNO),REML=FALSE))->b;
    summary(b)->b.summary;confint(b,method="b",nsim=1000) %>% suppressMessages()->b.confint;
    b.summary$coefficients[8,]->d;
    bind_rows(c,d) %>% suppressMessages()->c;
    with(a1,lmer(V1~Elapsed_months_2+mean_PASE_Total_score_categorize+Age+LEDD_sum+Disease_duration_symptom+Sex+(1+Elapsed_months_2|PATNO),REML=FALSE))->b.null;
    anova(b,b.null)->d
    append(p.value,d$`Pr(>Chisq)`[2])->p.value;
    append(Partner,i)->Partner;
    confint_sum<-bind_rows(confint_sum,b.confint[10,]) %>% as_tibble()
  }}
cbind(Partner,confint_sum,p.value) %>% cbind(c)->interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Total_score_categorize
write_csv(interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Total_score_categorize,"interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Total_score_categorize.csv")

a<-d4 %>% dplyr::select(Elapsed_months_2,Age,sum_PIGD_score,MSEADLG,mean_PASE_Work_score_binary,SDMT_correct,PATNO,Sex,LEDD_sum,Disease_duration_symptom)
c<-c()
p.value<-c()
Partner<-c()
Quantile<-c()
confint_sum<-c()
a$mean_PASE_Work_score_binary<-as.factor(a$mean_PASE_Work_score_binary)
for(i in colnames(a)){
  if((i!="Elapsed_months_2")&(i!="mean_PASE_Work_score_binary")&(i!="Age")&(i!="PATNO")&(i!="Sex")&(i!="LEDD_sum")&(i!="Disease_duration_symptom")){
    a %>% dplyr::select(i,Elapsed_months_2,mean_PASE_Work_score_binary,Age,PATNO,Sex,LEDD_sum,Disease_duration_symptom)->a1;
    colnames(a1)<-c("V1","Elapsed_months_2","mean_PASE_Work_score_categorize","Age","PATNO","Sex","LEDD_sum","Disease_duration_symptom");
    a1$V1<-scale(a1$V1,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Age<-scale(a1$Age,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Elapsed_months_2<-scale(a1$Elapsed_months_2,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$LEDD_sum<-scale(a1$LEDD_sum,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Disease_duration_symptom<-scale(a1$Disease_duration_symptom,center=T,scale=T);
    with(a1,lmer(V1~Elapsed_months_2*mean_PASE_Work_score_categorize+Age+LEDD_sum+Disease_duration_symptom+Sex+(1+Elapsed_months_2|PATNO),REML=FALSE))->b;
    summary(b)->b.summary;confint(b,method="b",nsim=1000) %>% suppressMessages()->b.confint;
    b.summary$coefficients[8,]->d;
    bind_rows(c,d) %>% suppressMessages()->c;
    with(a1,lmer(V1~Elapsed_months_2+mean_PASE_Work_score_categorize+Age+LEDD_sum+Disease_duration_symptom+Sex+(1+Elapsed_months_2|PATNO),REML=FALSE))->b.null;
    anova(b,b.null)->d
    append(p.value,d$`Pr(>Chisq)`[2])->p.value;
    append(Partner,i)->Partner;
    confint_sum<-bind_rows(confint_sum,b.confint[10,]) %>% as_tibble()
  }}
cbind(Partner,confint_sum,p.value) %>% cbind(c)->interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Work_score_categorize

write_csv(interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Work_score_categorize,"interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Work_score_categorize.csv")

a<-d4 %>% dplyr::select(Elapsed_months_2,Age,sum_PIGD_score,MSEADLG,mean_PASE_Work_score_binary,SDMT_correct,PATNO,Sex,LEDD_sum,Disease_duration_symptom)
c<-c()
p.value<-c()
Partner<-c()
Quantile<-c()
confint_sum<-c()
a$mean_PASE_Work_score_binary<-as.factor(a$mean_PASE_Work_score_binary)
for(i in colnames(a)){
  if((i!="Elapsed_months_2")&(i!="mean_PASE_Work_score_binary")&(i!="Age")&(i!="PATNO")&(i!="Sex")&(i!="LEDD_sum")&(i!="Disease_duration_symptom")){
    a %>% dplyr::select(i,Elapsed_months_2,mean_PASE_Work_score_binary,Age,PATNO,Sex,LEDD_sum,Disease_duration_symptom)->a1;
    colnames(a1)<-c("V1","Elapsed_months_2","mean_PASE_Work_score_categorize","Age","PATNO","Sex","LEDD_sum","Disease_duration_symptom");
    a1$V1<-scale(a1$V1,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Age<-scale(a1$Age,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Elapsed_months_2<-scale(a1$Elapsed_months_2,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$LEDD_sum<-scale(a1$LEDD_sum,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Disease_duration_symptom<-scale(a1$Disease_duration_symptom,center=T,scale=T);
    with(a1,lmer(V1~Elapsed_months_2*mean_PASE_Work_score_categorize+Age+LEDD_sum+Disease_duration_symptom+Sex+(1+Elapsed_months_2|PATNO),REML=FALSE))->b;
    summary(b)->b.summary;confint(b,method="b",nsim=1000) %>% suppressMessages()->b.confint;
    b.summary$coefficients[8,]->d;
    bind_rows(c,d) %>% suppressMessages()->c;
    with(a1,lmer(V1~Elapsed_months_2+mean_PASE_Work_score_categorize+Age+LEDD_sum+Disease_duration_symptom+Sex+(1+Elapsed_months_2|PATNO),REML=FALSE))->b.null;
    anova(b,b.null)->d
    append(p.value,d$`Pr(>Chisq)`[2])->p.value;
    append(Partner,i)->Partner;
    confint_sum<-bind_rows(confint_sum,b.confint[10,]) %>% as_tibble()
  }}
cbind(Partner,confint_sum,p.value) %>% cbind(c)->interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Work_score_categorize_2

write_csv(interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Work_score_categorize_2,"interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Work_score_categorize_2.csv")

a<-d4 %>% dplyr::select(Elapsed_months_2,Age,sum_PIGD_score,MSEADLG,mean_PASE_Household_score_binary,SDMT_correct,PATNO,Sex,LEDD_sum,Disease_duration_symptom)
c<-c()
p.value<-c()
Partner<-c()
Quantile<-c()
confint_sum<-c()
a$mean_PASE_Household_score_binary<-as.factor(a$mean_PASE_Household_score_binary)
for(i in colnames(a)){
  if((i!="Elapsed_months_2")&(i!="mean_PASE_Household_score_binary")&(i!="Age")&(i!="PATNO")&(i!="Sex")&(i!="LEDD_sum")&(i!="Disease_duration_symptom")){
    a %>% dplyr::select(i,Elapsed_months_2,mean_PASE_Household_score_binary,Age,PATNO,Sex,LEDD_sum,Disease_duration_symptom)->a1;
    colnames(a1)<-c("V1","Elapsed_months_2","mean_PASE_Household_score_categorize","Age","PATNO","Sex","LEDD_sum","Disease_duration_symptom");
    a1$V1<-scale(a1$V1,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Age<-scale(a1$Age,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Elapsed_months_2<-scale(a1$Elapsed_months_2,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$LEDD_sum<-scale(a1$LEDD_sum,center=T,scale=T);
    a1$Disease_duration_symptom<-scale(a1$Disease_duration_symptom,center=T,scale=T);
    with(a1,lmer(V1~Elapsed_months_2*mean_PASE_Household_score_categorize+Age+LEDD_sum+Disease_duration_symptom+Sex+(1+Elapsed_months_2|PATNO),REML=FALSE))->b;
    summary(b)->b.summary;confint(b,method="b",nsim=1000) %>% suppressMessages()->b.confint;
    b.summary$coefficients[8,]->d;
    bind_rows(c,d) %>% suppressMessages()->c;
    with(a1,lmer(V1~Elapsed_months_2+mean_PASE_Household_score_categorize+Age+LEDD_sum+Disease_duration_symptom+Sex+(1+Elapsed_months_2|PATNO),REML=FALSE))->b.null;
    anova(b,b.null)->d
    append(p.value,d$`Pr(>Chisq)`[2])->p.value;
    append(Partner,i)->Partner;
    confint_sum<-bind_rows(confint_sum,b.confint[10,]) %>% as_tibble()
  }}
cbind(Partner,confint_sum,p.value) %>% cbind(c)->interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Household_score_categorize
write_csv(interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Household_score_categorize,"interaction_effect_table_mean_PASE_Household_score_categorize.csv")


Sensitivity analysis (2): Missing data imputation

The following code describes the sensitivity analyses after missing data imputation. The following csvs are obtained: “imp_mean_PASE_Total_score.csv”, “imp_mean_PASE_Household_score.csv”, “imp_mean_PASE_Work_score.csv”, “imp_mean_PASE_Leisure_score.csv”, “imp_mean_AE.csv”.

UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS_PD_2<-UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS %>% filter(Group=="PD")
imp<-UPDRS_PASE_MOCA_ESS_MSEADL_RBDSQ_SCOPA_HVLT_JLO_LNS_SDMT_GDS_PD_2 %>% dplyr::select(PATNO,Sex,Elapsed_months_2,Age,LEDD_sum,sum_UPDRS_part3,sum_Tremor_score,sum_PIGD_score,MOCA_Total_score,HVLT_DELAYED_RECALL_T,JLO_RAW,LNS_RAW,SDMT_correct,SCOPA_total_score,GDS_total_score, ESS_total_score,RBDSQ_total_score,MSEADLG,Disease_duration_symptom)

IDS <- c("PATNO","Elapsed_months_2")
varIndex <- colnames(imp)

impute.out <- amelia(as.data.frame(imp[, varIndex]), idvars = IDS,noms = c("Sex"),m = 100)
names(impute.out$imputations)<-c(1:100)

Partner<-c()
c<-c()
imp_num<-c()
for(s in seq(1,100)){
  a<-impute.out$imputations[s] %>% as.data.frame();colnames(a)<-colnames(imp);
  a<-cbind(a,mean_PASE_Total_score) %>% as_tibble() %>% na.omit();
  a %>% dplyr::select(PATNO,Sex,Elapsed_months_2,mean_PASE_Total_score,Age,LEDD_sum,sum_UPDRS_part3,sum_Tremor_score,sum_PIGD_score,MOCA_Total_score,HVLT_DELAYED_RECALL_T,JLO_RAW,LNS_RAW,SDMT_correct,SCOPA_total_score,GDS_total_score, ESS_total_score,RBDSQ_total_score,MSEADLG,Disease_duration_symptom)
  for(i in colnames(a)){
    if((i!="Elapsed_months_2")&(i!="mean_PASE_Total_score")&(i!="Age")&(i!="PATNO")&(i!="LEDD_sum")&(i!="Disease_duration_symptom")&(i!="Sex")){
      a %>% dplyr::select(i,Elapsed_months_2,mean_PASE_Total_score,Age,PATNO,LEDD_sum,Disease_duration_symptom,Sex)->a1;
      colnames(a1)<-c("V1","Elapsed_months_2","mean_PASE_Total_score","Age","PATNO","LEDD_sum","Disease_duration_symptom","Sex");
      a1$V1<-scale(a1$V1,center=T,scale=T);
      a1$mean_PASE_Total_score<-scale(a1$mean_PASE_Total_score,center=T,scale=T);
      a1$Age<-scale(a1$Age,center=T,scale=T);
      a1$Elapsed_months_2<-scale(a1$Elapsed_months_2,center=T,scale=T);
      a1$LEDD_sum<-scale(a1$LEDD_sum,center=T,scale=T);
      a1$Disease_duration_symptom<-scale(a1$Disease_duration_symptom,center=T,scale=T);
      with(a1,lmer(V1~Elapsed_months_2*mean_PASE_Total_score+Age+LEDD_sum+Disease_duration_symptom+Sex+(1+Elapsed_months_2|PATNO),REML=FALSE))->b;
      summary(b)->b.summary;confint(b,method="b",nsim=1000) %>% suppressMessages()->b.confint;b.confint[10,]->f;
      b.summary$coefficients[8,]->e;
      c(e[1],e[2],f[1],f[2])->d;
      bind_rows(c,d)->c;
      append(Partner,i)->Partner;
      imp_num<-append(imp_num,s)
    }}
}

imp_mean_PASE_Total_score<-cbind(imp_num,Partner,c)

estimate_lowconf<-c();estimate_highconf<-c();Partner_conf<-c();estimate_mean<-c();CI_low_mean<-c();CI_low_lowconf<-c();CI_low_highconf<-c();CI_high_mean<-c();CI_high_lowconf<-c();CI_high_highconf<-c()
for (i in unique(Partner)){
  imp_mean_PASE_Total_score %>% dplyr::filter(Partner==i) ->a;estimate_mean<-append(estimate_mean,mean(a$Estimate));CI_high_mean<-append(CI_high_mean,mean(a$`97.5 %`));CI_low_mean<-append(CI_low_mean,mean(a$`2.5 %`))
  t.test(a$Estimate)->b;b$conf.int->b;estimate_lowconf<-append(estimate_lowconf,b[1]);estimate_highconf<-append(estimate_highconf,b[2]);Partner_conf<-append(Partner_conf,i);t.test(a$`2.5 %`)->b;b$conf.int->b;CI_low_lowconf<-append(CI_low_lowconf,b[1]);CI_low_highconf<-append(CI_low_highconf,b[2]);t.test(a$`97.5 %`)->b;b$conf.int->b;CI_high_lowconf<-append(CI_high_lowconf,b[1]);CI_high_highconf<-append(CI_high_highconf,b[2])
}

  imp_mean_PASE_Work_score %>% dplyr::filter(Partner==i) ->a;estimate_mean<-append(estimate_mean,mean(a$Estimate));CI_high_mean<-append(CI_high_mean,mean(a$`97.5 %`));CI_low_mean<-append(CI_low_mean,mean(a$`2.5 %`))
  t.test(a$Estimate)->b;b$conf.int->b;estimate_lowconf<-append(estimate_lowconf,b[1]);estimate_highconf<-append(estimate_highconf,b[2]);Partner_conf<-append(Partner_conf,i);t.test(a$`2.5 %`)->b;b$conf.int->b;CI_low_lowconf<-append(CI_low_lowconf,b[1]);CI_low_highconf<-append(CI_low_highconf,b[2]);t.test(a$`97.5 %`)->b;b$conf.int->b;CI_high_lowconf<-append(CI_high_lowconf,b[1]);CI_high_highconf<-append(CI_high_highconf,b[2])
}

imp_mean_PASE_Work_score<-data.frame(Partner=Partner_conf,`mean_PASE_Work_estimate_mean`=estimate_mean,`mean_PASE_Work_estimate_95%CI_low`=estimate_lowconf,`mean_PASE_Work_estimate_95%CI_high`=estimate_highconf,`mean_PASE_Work_CI_low_mean`=CI_low_mean,`mean_PASE_Work_CI_low_95%CI_low`=CI_low_lowconf,`mean_PASE_Work_CI_low_95%CI_high`=CI_low_highconf,`mean_PASE_Work_CI_high_mean`=CI_high_mean,`mean_PASE_Work_CI_high_95%CI_low`=CI_high_lowconf,`mean_PASE_Work_CI_high_95%CI_high`=CI_high_highconf)
imp_mean_PASE_Work_score<-interaction_effect_table_mean_final %>% dplyr::filter(class=="mean_PASE_Work_score") %>% dplyr::select(Partner,Estimate,`2.5 %`,`97.5 %`) %>% dplyr::left_join(imp_mean_PASE_Work_score,by = "Partner")




Partner<-c()
c<-c()
imp_num<-c()

for(s in seq(1,100)){
  a<-impute.out$imputations[s] %>% as.data.frame();colnames(a)<-colnames(imp);
  a<-cbind(a,mean_PASE_Leisure_score) %>% as_tibble() %>% na.omit();
  a %>% dplyr::select(PATNO,Sex,Elapsed_months_2,mean_PASE_Leisure_score,Age,LEDD_sum,sum_UPDRS_part3,sum_Tremor_score,sum_PIGD_score,MOCA_Total_score,HVLT_DELAYED_RECALL_T,JLO_RAW,LNS_RAW,SDMT_correct,SCOPA_total_score,GDS_total_score, ESS_total_score,RBDSQ_total_score,MSEADLG,Disease_duration_symptom)
  for(i in colnames(a)){
    if((i!="Elapsed_months_2")&(i!="mean_PASE_Leisure_score")&(i!="Age")&(i!="PATNO")&(i!="LEDD_sum")&(i!="Disease_duration_symptom")&(i!="Sex")){
      a %>% dplyr::select(i,Elapsed_months_2,mean_PASE_Leisure_score,Age,PATNO,LEDD_sum,Disease_duration_symptom,Sex)->a1;
      colnames(a1)<-c("V1","Elapsed_months_2","mean_PASE_Leisure_score","Age","PATNO","LEDD_sum","Disease_duration_symptom","Sex");
      a1$V1<-scale(a1$V1,center=T,scale=T);
      a1$mean_PASE_Leisure_score<-scale(a1$mean_PASE_Leisure_score,center=T,scale=T);
      a1$Age<-scale(a1$Age,center=T,scale=T);
      a1$Elapsed_months_2<-scale(a1$Elapsed_months_2,center=T,scale=T);
      a1$LEDD_sum<-scale(a1$LEDD_sum,center=T,scale=T);
      a1$Disease_duration_symptom<-scale(a1$Disease_duration_symptom,center=T,scale=T);
      with(a1,lmer(V1~Elapsed_months_2*mean_PASE_Leisure_score+Age+LEDD_sum+Disease_duration_symptom+Sex+(1+Elapsed_months_2|PATNO),REML=FALSE))->b;
      summary(b)->b.summary;confint(b,method="b",nsim=1000) %>% suppressMessages()->b.confint;b.confint[10,]->f;
      b.summary$coefficients[8,]->e;
      c(e[1],e[2],f[1],f[2])->d;
      bind_rows(c,d)->c;
      append(Partner,i)->Partner;
      imp_num<-append(imp_num,s)
    }}
}

imp_mean_PASE_Leisure_score<-cbind(imp_num,Partner,c)

estimate_lowconf<-c();estimate_highconf<-c();Partner_conf<-c();estimate_mean<-c();CI_low_mean<-c();CI_low_lowconf<-c();CI_low_highconf<-c();CI_high_mean<-c();CI_high_lowconf<-c();CI_high_highconf<-c()
for (i in unique(Partner)){
  imp_mean_PASE_Leisure_score %>% dplyr::filter(Partner==i) ->a;estimate_mean<-append(estimate_mean,mean(a$Estimate));CI_high_mean<-append(CI_high_mean,mean(a$`97.5 %`));CI_low_mean<-append(CI_low_mean,mean(a$`2.5 %`))
  t.test(a$Estimate)->b;b$conf.int->b;estimate_lowconf<-append(estimate_lowconf,b[1]);estimate_highconf<-append(estimate_highconf,b[2]);Partner_conf<-append(Partner_conf,i);t.test(a$`2.5 %`)->b;b$conf.int->b;CI_low_lowconf<-append(CI_low_lowconf,b[1]);CI_low_highconf<-append(CI_low_highconf,b[2]);t.test(a$`97.5 %`)->b;b$conf.int->b;CI_high_lowconf<-append(CI_high_lowconf,b[1]);CI_high_highconf<-append(CI_high_highconf,b[2])
}

imp_mean_PASE_Leisure_score<-data.frame(Partner=Partner_conf,`mean_PASE_Leisure_estimate_mean`=estimate_mean,`mean_PASE_Leisure_estimate_95%CI_low`=estimate_lowconf,`mean_PASE_Leisure_estimate_95%CI_high`=estimate_highconf,`mean_PASE_Leisure_CI_low_mean`=CI_low_mean,`mean_PASE_Leisure_CI_low_95%CI_low`=CI_low_lowconf,`mean_PASE_Leisure_CI_low_95%CI_high`=CI_low_highconf,`mean_PASE_Leisure_CI_high_mean`=CI_high_mean,`mean_PASE_Leisure_CI_high_95%CI_low`=CI_high_lowconf,`mean_PASE_Leisure_CI_high_95%CI_high`=CI_high_highconf)
imp_mean_PASE_Leisure_score<-interaction_effect_table_mean_final %>% dplyr::filter(class=="mean_PASE_Leisure_score") %>% dplyr::select(Partner,Estimate,`2.5 %`,`97.5 %`) %>% dplyr::left_join(imp_mean_PASE_Leisure_score,by = "Partner")
